  "scientific_decision": "dynamic_public_oracle_is_a_negative_stress_test_for_trial_collapsed_features_not_a_failed_dataset",
  "interpretation": [
    "The dynamic oracle tier has public nonzero responses, but no repeated exact videos, so repeat reliability is not estimable from this split.",
    "The transparent trial-collapsed video descriptor often beats a scrambled-stimulus control, but it does not beat the train mean response baseline.",
    "This supports the framework distinction between prediction above a weak control, reproducibility evidence, and mechanistic identifiability."
  ],
  "important_limitations": [
    "live_test and final_test tiers contain withheld zero responses in this public competition release",
    "oracle is the public held-out tier used here for framework consistency, not official competition scoring",
    "the baseline collapses temporal video and neural responses to trial-level descriptors, so it is a transparent stress test rather than a modern video model",
    "a publishable predictive result on Dynamic Sensorium requires a temporal/video model or official Sensorium-style model adapter"
  ]
